In [117]:
def Viterbi(data,train_index,test_index):

    #training
    Prior_Prob={}
    Initial_POS_Tag={}
    Total_Tag_Count={}
    Emission_Prob={}
    Transition_Prob={}
    Transition_POS_Count={}
    Emission_Word_Count={}
    #Training Phase (Parameter Estimation)
    for i in train_index:
        #Computing Initial Probabilities(Prob that Sentence starts per Tag)
        if data[i][0][1] not in Initial_POS_Tag:
            Initial_POS_Tag[data[i][0][1]]=1
        else:
            Initial_POS_Tag[data[i][0][1]]+=1
        flag=0
        prevTag=''
        for j in data[i]:
            #Computing Total Number of Words in Tags in train Corpus
            if j[1] not in Total_Tag_Count:
                Total_Tag_Count[j[1]]=1
            else:
                Total_Tag_Count[j[1]]+=1
            #Computing Total Number of Words by Tag in train Corpus
            if j[0] not in Emission_Word_Count:
                Emission_Word_Count[j[0]]={}
                Emission_Word_Count[j[0]][j[1]]=1
            else:
                if j[1] not in Emission_Word_Count[j[0]]:
                    Emission_Word_Count[j[0]][j[1]]=1
                else:
                    Emission_Word_Count[j[0]][j[1]]+=1
            #Computing Total Number of Times Tag at i+1th position is succedded by Tag at ith postion
            if flag==1:
                if prevTag not in Transition_POS_Count:
                    Transition_POS_Count[prevTag]={}
                    Transition_POS_Count[prevTag][j[1]]=1
                else:
                    if j[1] not in Transition_POS_Count[prevTag]:
                        Transition_POS_Count[prevTag][j[1]]=1
                    else:
                        Transition_POS_Count[prevTag][j[1]]+=1
            else:
                flag=1
            prevTag=j[1]

    #Computing Prior Prb
    for i in Initial_POS_Tag.keys():
        Prior_Prob[i]=((Initial_POS_Tag[i])/(len(train_index)))

    #Computing Emission Prob
    for i in Emission_Word_Count.keys():
        Emission_Prob[i]={}
        for j in Emission_Word_Count[i].keys():
            Emission_Prob[i][j]=((Emission_Word_Count[i][j])/(Total_Tag_Count[j]))

    #Computing Transition Prob
    for i in Transition_POS_Count.keys():
        Transition_Prob[i]={}
        for j in Transition_POS_Count[i].keys():
            Transition_Prob[i][j]=((Transition_POS_Count[i][j])/(Total_Tag_Count[i]))

    Prediction_Count={}
    for i in Total_Tag_Count.keys():
        Prediction_Count[i]={}
        for j in Total_Tag_Count.keys():
            Prediction_Count[i][j]=0

    All_Pos=list(Prior_Prob.keys())

    #Testing
    Predicted_Pos = []
    Actual_Pos=[]

    for i in test_index:
        sentence = data[i]
        T = len(sentence)
        State_Seq = []
        State_Prob = {}
        Actual_Pos.append([j[1] for j in data[i]])

        first_word = sentence[0][0]
        if first_word in Emission_Prob.keys():
            for tag in Emission_Prob[first_word].keys():
                prob = Prior_Prob[tag] * Emission_Prob[first_word][tag]
                State_Prob[tag] = prob
        else:
            for tag in Prior_Prob.keys():
                prob = Prior_Prob[tag] * 1e-6  # Use a small positive value for unknown words
                State_Prob[tag] = prob
        pos = max(State_Prob, key=State_Prob.get)
        State_Seq.append(pos)

        for word_position in range(1, T):
            new_State_Prob = {}
            for k in State_Prob.keys():
                word = sentence[word_position][0]
                prob = State_Prob[k]
                for transit in Transition_Prob[k].keys():
                    emit_prob = Emission_Prob.get(word, {}).get(transit, 1e-6) # Use a small positive value for unknown words
                    new_prob = prob * Transition_Prob[k][transit] * emit_prob
                    if transit not in new_State_Prob.keys() or new_prob > new_State_Prob[transit]:
                        new_State_Prob[transit] = new_prob
            # Update State_Prob for the next word position
            State_Prob = new_State_Prob
            # Append most probable POS tag for the current word based on Viterbi
            pos = max(State_Prob, key=State_Prob.get)
            State_Seq.append(pos)

        # Append the predicted POS sequence
        Predicted_Pos.append(State_Seq)

    return(Actual_Pos,Predicted_Pos,All_Pos)
In [118]:
#Cross Validation Training and Testing
kf = KFold(n_splits=5)

Confusion_Matrices=[]
Accuracy_Matrices=[]
Accuracy_Scores=[]

for i, (train_index, test_index) in enumerate(kf.split(data)):
    train_dummy=train_index
    test_dummy=test_index
    (Actual_Pos,Predicted_Pos,All_Pos)=Viterbi(data,train_index,test_index)

    
    Accuracy_Pos={}
    Total_Pos_words={}
    Confusion_Matrix={}
    for t in All_Pos:
        Accuracy_Pos[t]=0
        Total_Pos_words[t]=0
        Confusion_Matrix[t]={}
        for g in All_Pos:
            Confusion_Matrix[t][g]=0

    Total_words=0
    for t in Actual_Pos:
        for j in t:
            Total_Pos_words[j]+=1
            Total_words+=1
    for r in range(len(Predicted_Pos)):
        for j in range(len(Predicted_Pos[r])):
            if Actual_Pos[r][j]==Predicted_Pos[r][j]:
                Accuracy_Pos[Actual_Pos[r][j]]+=1
            Confusion_Matrix[Actual_Pos[r][j]][Predicted_Pos[r][j]]+=1
    #Computing Accuracy per POS Tag
    for r in Accuracy_Pos:
        Accuracy_Pos[r]=Accuracy_Pos[r]/Total_Pos_words[r]
    #Computing Confusion Matrix values
    Total_Correct_Pos_Count=0 
    for z in Confusion_Matrix.keys():
        Total_Correct_Pos_Count+=Confusion_Matrix[z][z]
        for f in Confusion_Matrix[z].keys():
            Confusion_Matrix[z][f]=Confusion_Matrix[z][f]/Total_words

    column_sum={}
    for z in Confusion_Matrix.keys():
        io=0
        for f in Confusion_Matrix[z].keys():
            io+=Confusion_Matrix[z][f]
        column_sum[z]=io
        
    for z in Confusion_Matrix.keys():
        for f in Confusion_Matrix[z].keys():
            Confusion_Matrix[z][f]=Confusion_Matrix[z][f]/column_sum[z]
    #OverallAccuracy
    Acc= Total_Correct_Pos_Count/Total_words
    Confusion_Matrices.append(Confusion_Matrix)
    Accuracy_Matrices.append(Accuracy_Pos)
    Accuracy_Scores.append(Acc)
    print(str(i+1)+"st/rd/th split Accuracy ")
    print(Acc)
mean_acc = sum(Accuracy_Scores)/len(Accuracy_Scores)

    Precision_per_Tag[i]=0
    Recall_per_Tag_1[i]=0
    row_sum=0
    col_sum=0
    for j in temp[i].keys():
        row_sum+=temp[i][j]

Final_Recall=sum(Mean_Recall_V)/5

Final_Recall_Per_Tag={}
Final_F1_Score_Per_Tag={}
for i in temp.keys():
    Final_Precision_Per_Tag[i]=0
    Final_Recall_Per_Tag[i]=0
    Final_F1_Score_Per_Tag[i]=0
for i in range(len(Precision_Tag_V)):
    for j in Precision_Tag_V[i]:
        Final_Precision_Per_Tag[j]+=Precision_Tag_V[i][j]
        Final_Recall_Per_Tag[j]+=Recall_Tag_V[i][j]
for i in temp.keys():
    Final_Precision_Per_Tag[i]=Final_Precision_Per_Tag[i]/5
    Final_Recall_Per_Tag[i]=Final_Recall_Per_Tag[i]/5
    Final_F1_Score_Per_Tag[i]=(2*Final_Precision_Per_Tag[i]*Final_Recall_Per_Tag[i])/(Final_Precision_Per_Tag[i]+Final_Recall_Per_Tag[i])
Final_F1_score=(2*Final_Precision*Final_Recall)/(Final_Recall+Final_Precision)
Final_F2_score = (5 * Final_Precision * Final_Recall) / (4 * Final_Precision + Final_Recall)
Final_F05_score = (1.25 * Final_Precision * Final_Recall) / (0.25 * Final_Precision + Final_Recall)
